name: South Africa vs Nepal
summary: South Africa and Nepal faced off in a crucial T20 World Cup group match, with Nepal electing to field first. The live stream of the match was available on various platforms. However, the match between Sri Lanka and Nepal was abandoned due to rain. South Africa's spinner Keshav Maharaj was replaced by Tabraiz Shamsi for the match against Nepal, while Nepal's star leg-spinner Sandeep Lamichhane returned to the playing XI. Due to the rainout, South Africa advanced to the Super Eights after the match against Nepal was abandoned. South Africa scored 115/7 against Nepal, with David Miller getting dismissed during the match. Despite a slow start, Tristan Stubbs kept South Africa in the game, and the onus was on him to guide them to a competitive total.

summary: In the Super Rugby Pacific semi-finals, the Auckland Blues triumphed over the ACT Brumbies 34-20, securing a spot in the championship match. The Brumbies, who were playing their final home game before disbanding, were praised for their resilience despite being outplayed by the Blues' physicality. Rob Valetini of the Brumbies stood out with an impressive performance, while the Blues' win extends Australia's Super Rugby title drought. The Blues will now face the winner of the Crusaders and Hurricanes match in the final, while the Brumbies' departure marks the end of an era for Australian rugby.
